						               													<description>&amp;quot;Virus&amp;quot; is a fun board game where you battle to spread infection around the world. You act like a Virus and you lead a tactical fight. Each player is one Virus and your goal is to defeat other players and conquer the world. &amp;#10;The game is simple enough that it can be learned and played in a short time, and the battles are different each time you play a new game. This is a game for 2-6 players and co-operative play. Experienced players should be able to finish one game in 40-60 minutes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Objective&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 3 ways to win:&amp;#10;1. Termination: defeat all players.&amp;#10;2. Domination: conquer 30 cities.&amp;#10;3. Days of Infection: conquer the most number of cities after certain number of days (turns).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Components&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1. A quad-folded map of the world&amp;#10;2. 6 dice (6 different colors)&amp;#10;3. 240 tokens (6 different colors, 40 tokens for each player)&amp;#10;4. The manual in full color with rules and lots of examples of play&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Setup&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game can be played in following setups and modes:&amp;#10;1. 2-6 players (each player on his own).&amp;#10;2. 2 vs. 2 or 3 vs. 3 or 2 vs. 2 vs. 2 (co-operative play).&amp;#10;3. One or two experienced players could play against a greater number of rookie players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Playing the game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players take turns and all other actions in clockwise order.&amp;#10;Each day have 4 possible Actions:&amp;#10;1. Do nothing: player skips his day.&amp;#10;2. Infect: player on his day places only once a token on free city adjacent to his conquered city.&amp;#10;3. Bonus: player on his day places Bonus tokens on free cities adjacent to his conquered cities.&amp;#10;4. Attack: player attacks adjacent enemy tokens.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
